Install Git:
------------
sudo apt-get update -y
sudo apt-get install git -y

Configure Git:
--------------
git config --global user.name "Deepak"
git config --global user.email "abc@example.com"
git config --global core.editor "vim"

Git Basic Commands:
-------------------
mkdir demo
cd demo
git init
git add .
git status
git commit -m "First Commit"
git status
git log
git diff

Case Study:
------------
 Create a local git repository and move the entire code base to it
Move to your Source Code directory and initialize a git repo in that folder
ls
git init
git add .
git status
git commit -m "Initial Commit"
git log

 Create a new branch for a new feature you want to add to the application
git branch new-feature1
git branch
git checkout new-feature1
git diff
git add index.html
git commit -m "Commit in new-feature1 branch"

 Merge back the created branch with the master branch
git checkout master
git merge new-feature1

 Create a remote repository
Create an account on github.com
Now create a repository
git remote add origin https://github.com/<REPOSITORY URL>
git log
git push -u origin master
 Push the local repository to companys remote repository
Verify from the UI now



git push origin master --allow-unrelated-histories
